IBADAN  – Oyo state’s Commis­sioner for Budget and Eco­nomic Planning, Professor Musbau Adetunji Baba­tunde has declared that the preparation of a 20-year-de­velopment plan christened Agenda 2040 encapsulating year 2021-2040 for optimal development. Adetunji made the dec­laration during the zonal consultative meeting in­forming the populace about the development plan held at the Ibadan North-East Local Government Mar­riage Registry-hall. The Commissioner, during the forum said the plan would birth initiatives for trade consisting of Ag­riculture, Gold-mining, Ed­ucation, health policies for people’s stability and secu­rity for enabling business environment. Jealous Lover Kills Girlfriend For Flirting With Customer In… Lassa Fever Kills 40 Persons In 30 Days – NCDC In their respective good­will messages, Chairman, Ibadan North-East Local Government, Ibrahim Akintayo, noted that the meeting is premised on people’s needs and wants for an improved standard of living. This is just as Akintayo said infrastructural facil­ities are developed for the people since leaders are accountable to them, hence the need for transparency in daily dealings of gover­nance which must entail public opinion, as affirmed by the Chairman of Ibadan South-East local govern­ment, Emmanuel Alawode and Ibadan-North’s local Government chairman, Shaib Yusuf.